        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Psalm 70:3",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " ( equals  ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Psalm 40:15",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ") יחד and לספּותהּ are given up entirely; the original is more full-toned and soaring. Instead of ישׁמּוּ, torpescant, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Psalm 70:4",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " has ישׁוּבוּ, recedant (as in ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Psalm 6:11",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", cf. ",
        "children": []
      },
